7.4 Update API URL
In src/App.js, find this line (near the top):
const API_URL = 'http://localhost:5000';
For now, leave it as is for local testing. Later you'll change it to your Railway URL.
7.5 Test Frontend Locally
In your terminal (inside facebook-clone-frontend folder):
npm start
Wait for it to open in browser (http://localhost:3000)
Try:
Click "Sign Up"
Create a test account
Write a post
Refresh page - post should still be there!
Try liking posts
If this works, your frontend works! ‚úÖ
PART 8: CHANGE API URL TO RAILWAY (2 MINUTES)
8.1 Update App.js
In src/App.js, change this line:
const API_URL = 'http://localhost:5000';
To:
const API_URL = 'https://facebook-clone-backend-production.up.railway.app';
Replace with your actual Railway URL from Part 6, Step 6.3
8.2 Test Again
In terminal:
npm start
Go to http://localhost:3000 and test again. Your frontend should now connect to the live backend!
If it works, everything is connected! ‚úÖ
PART 9: UPLOAD FRONTEND TO GITHUB (5 MINUTES)
9.1 Create GitHub Repository
Go to: https://github.com/new
Repository name: facebook-clone-frontend
Description: "Facebook clone frontend"
Choose Public
Click "Create repository"
9.2 Upload Your Code
In terminal (inside facebook-clone-frontend folder):
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/facebook-clone-frontend.git
git push -u origin main
Replace YOUR_USERNAME with your GitHub username.
9.3 Verify
Go to: https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/facebook-clone-frontend
You should see all your files there!
‚úÖ Frontend uploaded
PART 10: DEPLOY FRONTEND TO VERCEL (5 MINUTES)
10.1 Connect and Deploy
Go to: https://vercel.com/dashboard
Click "New Project"
Click "Import GitHub Project"
Search for facebook-clone-frontend
Click on it
Click "Import"
Click "Deploy"
Wait 2-3 minutes for deployment
10.2 Get Your Live URL
After deployment finishes, you'll see your URL:
https://facebook-clone-frontend-YOUR_NAME.vercel.app
Your app is LIVE! üöÄ
PART 11: FINAL TEST (5 MINUTES)
11.1 Test Your Live App
Go to your Vercel URL
Click "Sign Up"
Create a test account
Write a post
Refresh page - post should appear!
Try liking and commenting
If everything works, YOU'RE DONE! üéâ
TROUBLESHOOTING
Problem: Backend won't connect to MongoDB
Check your MongoDB password in .env
Go to MongoDB Atlas ‚Üí Network Access ‚Üí Make sure your IP is whitelisted
Problem: Frontend can't reach backend
Check your Railway URL is correct in App.js
Make sure it starts with https:// not http://
Problem: Deployment fails
Check all files are pushed to GitHub
Check .env variables are set on Railway/Vercel
Check package.json has all dependencies
Problem: Something else?
Check the browser console (F12) for errors
Check the terminal for error messages
Make sure all steps were completed in order
NEXT STEPS - ADD MORE FEATURES
Once everything works, add:
User profiles - See user info and their posts
Follow system - Follow/unfollow users
Direct messaging - Send private messages
Image uploads - Upload photos with posts
Search - Find posts and users
Notifications - See who liked your posts
Dark mode - Toggle dark/light theme
